## Acknowledgements

This project implements optimization-based whole-body control for the THOR
34-DOF humanoid robot, developed by Virginia Tech RoMeLa and TREC Labs.

Theoretical foundations are based on the following seminal works:

- Hopkins, M.A. & Leonessa, A. (2015). "Optimization-Based Whole-Body Control
  of a Series Elastic Humanoid Robot." Int. J. Humanoid Robotics, 12(3).
- Orin, D.E., Goswami, A. & Lee, S.-H. (2013). "Centroidal Dynamics of a
  Humanoid Robot." Autonomous Robots, 35(2-3), 161-176.
- Escande, A., Mansard, N. & Wieber, P.-B. (2014). "Hierarchical Quadratic
  Programming." Int. J. Robotics Research, 33(7), 1006-1028.
- Meduri, A. et al. (2023). "BiConMP: A Nonlinear Model Predictive Control
  Framework for Whole Body Motion Planning." IEEE Trans. Robotics, 39(2).
- Posa, M., Cantu, C. & Tedrake, R. (2014). "A Direct Method for Trajectory
  Optimization of Rigid Bodies Through Contact." IJRR, 33(1), 69-81.
- Featherstone, R. (2008). "Rigid Body Dynamics Algorithms." Springer.

Special thanks to the open-source communities behind NumPy, SciPy, Numba,
and Matplotlib.
